-- Knicks Defeat Celtics 85-78 in First Game of Their NBA Playoffs
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-04-20T21:35:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-20/knicks-defeat-celtics-85-78-in-first-game-of-their-nba-playoffs.html
The  New York  Knicks defeated the
Boston Celtics 85-78 to take a 1-0 lead in their National
Basketball Association best-of-seven playoff series.  In the second Eastern Conference game today, the Brooklyn
Nets host the Chicago Bulls.  Carmelo Anthony scored 36 points to rally the Knicks from a
53-49 halftime deficit on their home court at Madison Square
Garden. The Knicks held the Celtics to eight points in the
fourth quarter.  Jeff Green led the Celtics with 26 points.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nancy Kercheval at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net  